[Main]
Keywords=auto

[Description]
Defines a local variable as having a local lifetime.

[Explanation]
Keyword <CODE>auto</CODE> uses the following syntax:
<PRE>[auto] <I>data-definition</I>;
</PRE>
As the local lifetime is the default for local variables, <CODE>auto</CODE> keyword is
extremely rarely used.
<BR><BR>
<B>Note:</B> GNU C extends <CODE>auto</CODE> keyword to allow forward declaration of
<A HREF="$$INFOLINK(gnuexts/SEC66)">nested functions</A>.
